. Sternite VIII (Fig. 
78
) band-like, narrowed on distal half; strongly and widely notched at anterior margin forming two inclined lobes near middle; emargination reaching distal half of sternite length; long setae disposed on each distal lobe. Sternite IX (Fig. 
75
) elongate, elliptical, widened at middle, with both extremities rounded; moderately long setae disposed on distal fifth. Tergite IX (Fig. 
77
) transverse, moderately narrowed to apex; distal margin strongly and widely notched at middle; emargination surpassing half of tergite length; punctated larterally near base; tergite X elongate, slightly narrowed apicad; inserted at tergite IX apex; distal margin rounded; distal area microspined.
